OPEN_RES_MASS.statement:
Prove one of the following for ledger residual R(z) at deployed KB-MCA a+=1116048 (not merely aperiodic proxy):
  (i)   max |R(z)| ≤ TARGET;
  (ii)  max N_can_prim(z) ≤ floor(TARGET/17);
  (iii) residual supports inject into a set of size ≤ n·p or ≤ t·p;
  (iv)  residual can-cores inject into a set of size ≤ floor(TARGET/17) or ≤ n·p or ≤ t;
  (v)   M_m^{res} ≤ 1 and U_phi ≤ floor(TARGET/17) (or U_res with side routing).
Any one upgrades Route-D conditional closure toward residual atom (still subject to other first-match branches for full U≤B*).

north_star.statement:
The Route-D north star is residual mass for ledger residual R(z) at KB-MCA a+=1116048 (first-match residual of j-supports), not global multi-mate taxonomy. Sufficient forms include:
  (K_rem) max_z |R(z)| ≤ TARGET (residual flatness / pack atom);
  (E1)    |G_gen_support| + |D_full_rank_prim| ≤ t·p;
  (E2)    residual supports inject into a set of size ≤ t·p;
  (E5)    residual supports inject into D × F_p (size n·p).
Covering+routing reduce (K_rem) to bounds on N_can_prim, U_res, M_m^{res}, or U_phi (v4–v11). Multi-mate geometry (v8–v13) only constrains M_m / M_m^{res} structure; it does not replace mass.
